        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 12:56PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility to
less than a quarter of a mile. This band of heavy snow is producing
extremely heavy snow at the rate of 1 to 2 inches per hour. This band
of heavy snow is so intense that it is producing lightning and
thunder and possibly small hail. The snow will accumulate very
rapidly.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 1256 PM MDT, a band of heavy snow was
along a line extending from 20 miles north of Norwood to 7 miles east
of Nucla to 9 miles south of Naturita and moving southeast at 20 MPH.

THIS BAND OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Norwood around 110 PM MDT.

This includes the following highways...
Colorado 141 between mile markers 41 and 56.
Colorado 145 between mile markers 99 and 116.

SAFETY INFO...
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this band of
heavy snow. Rapid changes in visibility and potentially slick roads
may lead to accidents.
</description>
